transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Hello, I would like to cancel my prescription, please.

Speaker 1: Okay, let me pull the prescription.

Speaker 2: Mr. Chad?

Speaker 1: Yep, Chad Shipley.

Speaker 2: Shipley.

Speaker 1: Yes, I see you have a prescription

Speaker 2: for Viagra 15 milligram, 10 tablets.

Speaker 1: Yeah, and I think the doctor wrote it on,

Speaker 2: I think every 30 days.

Speaker 1: Any health concern or you just trying to order as needed?

Speaker 2: You don't want to go based on the 30 days?

Speaker 1: Yeah, I wanted to order as needed

Speaker 2: and so I don't want to have them sent unless I need them.

Speaker 1: Okay, so I'm gonna stop the 30 day supply from the doctor.

Speaker 2: Tell the pharmacy they pause you up to half a year

Speaker 1: so you're not on a monthly and you can call to reorder.

Speaker 2: And if you get, I think a minimum of two refill a year,

Speaker 1: they're always gonna maintain the price

Speaker 2: that you have right now, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah, not a problem.

Speaker 2: So I'm just gonna stop the monthly.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: And pause the prescription so the consultation

Speaker 1: is still available and you can access the prescription.

Speaker 2: Perfect, thank you.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right, you're all set, okay?

Speaker 2: Your prescription has been paused, okay?

Speaker 1: Perfect, thank you very much.

Speaker 2: I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: You're welcome.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: All right, bye.
